Everything was amazing except for my experience with their delivery, which according to reviews both here and on Yelp seems to be a common issue.  I placed an order on Ubereats around 8pm and my food didn't arrive until 10. A driver was paired with the order around 8:30 I assume because at 8:45 he was already at the restaurant waiting to pick it up. But at 9pm the driver was unpaired from the order and Uber sent me a notification saying the order was going to be late due to a delay in finding a driver. That obviously confused me because the driver had already been there for quite some time waiting for the order so I contacted support. They told me the driver left because the line inside was incredibly long and my food had yet to be prepared. It wasn't until around 9:30 that another driver was paired and arrived at the restaurant. Another 10 minutes of him waiting went by so I decided to call the restaurant myself to see what the holdup was. Apparently my order had JUST started to be prepared, 1.5 hours after the order was confirmed. 15 minutes later the order was on the way, thank God the driver didnt leave because I probably would've been eating at midnight.  Besides all that mess, the food was very, very good. Still very hot when it arrived, salmon was tender, shrimp were perfectly cooked and cleaned, potatoes and corn on point, everything wonderfully seasoned to perfection. I would've liked the broccoli to have a little more crunch but they steamed everything together so I understood. I just hope that they see what people are saying in regards to their delivery times and make a change. The man I spoke with said verbatim that they had tons of orders coming in along with walk ins which is why my order was prepared an hour and a half after it coming into their system. If y'all are slammed, stop taking orders until you're caught up. People will understand. I beg of y'all to work on that cause you're missing out on great reviews for things that have nothing to do with the amazing quality of your food.

Now I waited yet again(very patient I know) and after being forgotten, I asked again what is taking so long with my order, it doesn't take 2 hrs to steam crablegs!?! The chef now asks what did you order? I gave him the receipt which had my order number hand written very  big by the lady whom took my payment. After searching he couldn't find it either. He then asked another young lady who then finally remembered that she accidentally gave my order to an uber eats pick up! I didn't even have the strength to get upset, at this point I just wanted a refund! My 6yr old is hungry and I wanted to leave. TERRIBLE experience for my first time there. My suggestion is,for such a busy spot they need to have a designated person to handle the uber pick ups to avoid mishaps like these.
